article.description: Cal Poly holds on for 58-56 win over CS-Fullerton
article.headline: Cal Poly holds on for 58-56 win over CS-Fullerton
article.linkText: Cal Poly holds on for 58-56 win over CS-Fullerton
article.story: FULLERTON, Calif. -- Jamal Johnson scored 12 points and Brian Bennett added 10 as Cal Poly edged Cal State-Fullerton for a 58-56 win on Thursday night. Joel Awich hit a 3-pointer to give Cal Poly (8-10, 4-1 Big West) a 58-53 lead with 3:05 remaining, but it turned out to be the last time the Mustangs scored. However, Cal Poly limited the Titans (6-12, 1-3) to just a point in the final 3 1/2 minutes to hold on for the win. Alex Harris missed a jumper which would have tied the game with 2 seconds left for Cal State Fullerton. Cal Poly scored 11 straight points early on, racing to a 17-5 lead. The Mustangs are off to its best Big West start in its program's 18 years as a conference member. Michael Williams led Cal State-Fullerton with 20 points.
